Below is a worked‐through example of how to interpret and rebuild the target “rocket” structure from the two reference images.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1.  ANALYSIS OF THE MAIN TARGET IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
• Total Block Count: 6  
  – One tall orange cylinder in the center.  
  – Two low orange wedges (one on each side).  
  – Two small blue rectangular blocks (one paired with each wedge).  
  – One orange “roof” (triangular prism) on top.  

• Layering:  
  – Bottom Layer (5 blocks):  
    1 cylinder at center,  
    2 wedges at left/right,  
    2 blue rectangular blocks adjacent to those wedges.  
  – Top Layer (1 block):  
    The orange triangular “roof” set on top of the cylinder.  

• Spatial Relationships:  
  – The tall orange cylinder stands upright in the middle.  
  – Each orange wedge sits to one side of the cylinder, with a small blue block abutting or partly resting on that wedge.  
  – A single triangular orange roof piece caps the top of the cylinder.  


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2.  SELECTING REQUIRED BLOCKS FROM THE DICTIONARY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
To match shape, color, and orientation exactly (without rotating blocks ourselves), use:

• 1 × Block #4  (Orange cylinder, vertical)  
• 1 × Block #8  (Orange triangular “roof”)  
• 1 × Block #11 (Orange wedge, oriented as on the right side)  
• 1 × Block #12 (Orange wedge, oriented as on the left side)  
• 1 × Block #1  (Blue rectangular block in the orientation matching the right‐side block)  
• 1 × Block #2  (Blue rectangular block in the orientation matching the left‐side block)  

These six blocks reproduce the exact forms and orientations seen in the rocket‐like target structure.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3.  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY ORDER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below is one possible order to place the six chosen blocks:

{
  "Step1": "Move block with index 4",
  "Step2": "Move block with index 12",
  "Step3": "Move block with index 2",
  "Step4": "Move block with index 11",
  "Step5": "Move block with index 1",
  "Step6": "Move block with index 8"
}

In this sequence,
• You first place the tall cylinder (#4).  
• Then position the left wedge (#12) and its blue block (#2).  
• Next place the right wedge (#11) with its blue block (#1).  
• Finally set the triangular roof block (#8) on top.
